cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with guessing numbers and information defect, which are concepts related to information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of logarithms and the analysis of asymptotic behavior suggest cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the explicit protocol presented in the paper involves communication and transmission of information, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
